  "question": "A 62-year-old fair lady presented to you with a 1 cm hard nodule fixed to nasal cartilage. A biopsy done revealed the cells arranged in nest, the outer layer giving a palisade arrangement and inner layers are polyhedral with large basophilic nuclei with minimal mitosis and no attempt at keratinization. The best management is:",
